textAfterTable: Install Method: iPC OS 10.5.6 Final PPF5 Kernel: 9.5.0 Voodoo BIOS Version: 2.1 BIOS Options: Disabled Serial, Parallel & MIDI Ports, No-Excute Memory Protection = Enabled, HPET Table = Enabled (not taking the Credit) Intel Dual Core E5200, 2GB DDR2 @667Mhz Audio: ALC888 in & out stereo working with VoodooHDA.kext LAN: ViaRhine (II) works (on customize Add Via Rhine Driver) IDE: Works SATA: Works Sleep, Shutdown & Restart Work "You can correct the Disk Mounting issue by matching your kernel with the proper seatbelt.kext build. If you have the 9.5.0 kernel you will need the Seatbelt.kext from 10.5.5 If you have the 9.6.0 kernel you will need the Seatbelt.kext from 10.5.6" iPC install contains 9.5.0 version, just add it at customize. Seatbelt.kext Issues so far: Only 1 CPU is active(CPUS=1 One Core Fix, some might need to start the install dvd with cpus=1 boot option) Fix for 1 CPU issue: download a modified bios, [6] choose file 4CoreDual-SATA2 v2.10 After you flashed the bios, you can simply install it without the need of the cpus=1 One Core fix, and can use both(or more) cores of your cpu ;) USB issue fix available or use customized patched USB Drivers
